<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-s7q_Kc9uZtw_NcnVJEoI6g" name="how_to_adopt_use_case_modelling,_n4-JINuNEd-pTLmXJigeaQ" guid="-s7q_Kc9uZtw_NcnVJEoI6g" changeDate="2011-06-27T13:33:21.957+0200">
  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Use case modelling&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/requirements_model.assign_44B2AD0C.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_jWhQIOG4Ed-AyrTFSpVP8g&quot;>Requirements model&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;identifies the system requirements. These include&#xD;
    functional requirements, &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/non_functional_requirements_65B5C8B8.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_xF0vkN0UEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>Non-functional requirements&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp; (quality of service) and constraints.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/non_functional_requirements_65B5C8B8.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_xF0vkN0UEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>Non-functional requirements&lt;/a> are statements concerning performance, availability,&#xD;
    security, reliability and so forth. There are also other requirements specifying constraints that will have impact on&#xD;
    the system to be developed, for instance available resources, special customer preferences, company strategy etc.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Use cases and scenario descriptions are used to capture the functional requirements. These use cases and scenario&#xD;
    descriptions are also used to structure some of the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/non_functional_requirements_65B5C8B8.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_xF0vkN0UEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>Non-functional requirements&lt;/a> and constraints. Figure 1 shows the work products of&#xD;
    the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/requirements_model.assign_44B2AD0C.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_jWhQIOG4Ed-AyrTFSpVP8g&quot;>Requirements model&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/requirements_model_work_products.png&quot; width=&quot;524&quot; height=&quot;235&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/requirements_model.assign_44B2AD0C.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_jWhQIOG4Ed-AyrTFSpVP8g&quot;>Requirements model&lt;/a> is primarily a UML use case model that describes the system in&#xD;
    terms of actors, use cases and scenario descriptions. The model contains the following work products:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/system_boundary_model_4296FE34.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_NUjPIN0VEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>System boundary model&lt;/a>. Identifies the system under consideration (area of&#xD;
        concern) and describes the system boundaries as well as the main services offered by the system.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/use_case_scenario_model_9DF725B1.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_SMZu4N0VEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>Use case scenario model&lt;/a>.&amp;nbsp;Includes more detailed descriptions of the system&#xD;
        resulting from further analysis using the common use case detailing technique, by diving into a use case&#xD;
        discovering new use cases and actors. &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Use case scenarios are also described in this work product.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/non_functional_requirements_65B5C8B8.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_xF0vkN0UEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>Non-functional requirements&lt;/a>. This work product identifies constraints, general&#xD;
        requirements and other kinds of &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/non_functional_requirements_65B5C8B8.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_xF0vkN0UEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>Non-functional requirements&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;not fitting into the previous work products of&#xD;
        the requirements model. &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
                href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/non_functional_requirements_65B5C8B8.html&quot;&#xD;
                 guid=&quot;_xF0vkN0UEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>Non-functional requirements&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;can be made part of the use case model&#xD;
                as these kinds of requirements are associated with use cases according to the use case template. General &lt;a&#xD;
                class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
                href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/non_functional_requirements_65B5C8B8.html&quot;&#xD;
                 guid=&quot;_xF0vkN0UEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>Non-functional requirements&lt;/a> that apply for the whole system are&#xD;
                associated with the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
                href=&quot;./../../../practice.requirements.use_case_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/system_boundary_model_4296FE34.html&quot;&#xD;
                 guid=&quot;_NUjPIN0VEd-xB8a51ZHHaA&quot;>System boundary model&lt;/a>.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
